<h2 id="_assignment_operators">Assignment operators</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The most basic assignment operator is "=". One might assume that it stands for "equals". However, this is not the case. Instead, this operator means that the value of the expression on the right is assigned to the operand on the left. Thus, the expression should be read as "is set to the value of".</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_single_line_code_block">Single-line code block</h3>
<div class="listingblock">
<div class="content">
<pre class="highlight"><code class="language-plenty" data-lang="plenty">&#123;&#37; $_a = 3 &#37;&#125;
&#123;&#37; $_a += 5 &#37;&#125;
{# sets $_a to the value 8 as if we had written: $_a = $_a + 5 #}

&#123;&#37; $_b = "Hello " &#37;&#125;
&#123;&#37; $_b .= "there!" &#37;&#125;
{# sets $_b to the value "Hello there!" #}</code></pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_multi_line_code_block">Multi-line code block</h3>
<div class="listingblock">
<div class="content">
<pre class="highlight"><code class="language-plenty" data-lang="plenty">&#123;&#37;
	$_a = 3;
	$_a += 5;

	# sets $_a to the value 8 as if we had written: $_a = $_a + 5


	$_b = "Hello ";
	$_b .= "there!";

	# sets $b to the value "Hello there!"
&#37;&#125;</code></pre>
</div>
</div>
