<h2 id="_operator_precedence">Operator precedence</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The operator precedence determines how an operator connects two expressions. Thus, the result of the expression <em>1 + 5 * 3</em> equals <em>16</em> and not <em>18</em> because the multiplication operator (*) precedes the addition operator (+). You can use brackets to influence operator precedence. Thus, <em>(1 + 5) * 3</em> equals <em>18</em>. If operators have equal priority, associativity from left to right is used.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The following table shows the operator’s precedence. The operators are listed in descending order. The operator with the highest precedence is at the top.</p>
